<!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>GEO, short for Generative Engine Optimisation, is the process of improving how your brand appears within AI-powered search results. It focuses on making your content readable, trusted and reference-worthy by large language models such as ChatGPT, Google\u2019s AI Overviews and Perplexity.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                              <div data-question-group>\n                          <div class=\"flex gap-4 mb-4\" data-question-ask>\n                            <strong>Did this answer your question?<\/strong>\n                            <span class=\"relative text-green cursor-pointer\" data-question=\"yes\">\n                              Yes\n                              <div class=\"faq-pop-up\" data-question-display=\"yes\">\n                                That\u2019s great glad we could help!\n                                <a href=\"\/contact-us\/\" target=\"_self\" class=\"btn btn-pink btn-small\" data-mp=\"\">\n                                  <span class=\"btn-bg\" data-mp-item=\"\" data-mp-scale=\"1.05\" data-mp-d=\"0.2\"><\/span>\n                                  <span class=\"btn-label\" data-mp-item=\"\">\n                                                                          Start a Project                                                                      <\/span>\n                                <\/a>\n                              <\/div>\n                            <\/span>\n                            <span class=\"relative text-red cursor-pointer\" data-question=\"no\">\n                              No\n                              <div class=\"faq-pop-up\" data-question-display=\"no\">\n                                No problem, one of our experts can give you a more in-depth answer.\n                                <a href=\"\/contact-us\/\" target=\"_self\" class=\"btn btn-pink btn-small\" data-mp=\"\">\n                                  <span class=\"btn-bg\" data-mp-item=\"\" data-mp-scale=\"1.05\" data-mp-d=\"0.2\"><\/span>\n                                  <span class=\"btn-label\" data-mp-item=\"\">Ask our Experts<\/span>\n                                <\/a>\n                              <\/div>\n                            <\/span>\n                          <\/div>\n                        <\/div>\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">What exactly is GEO and how is it different from SEO?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>GEO stands for Generative Engine Optimisation. It focuses on improving how AI systems read, interpret and reference your brand when producing answers. Traditional SEO is about ranking pages. GEO is about being understood as an entity and cited inside AI summaries. AI platforms do not rely on links or standard ranking factors. They rely on meaning, clarity, structure, semantic signals, external citations and entity strength. GEO sits alongside SEO but solves a very different problem: visibility inside AI generated results.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Why do AI engines struggle to understand most websites?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>Most websites are written only for humans. AI models need structured signals, clear entities, relationship cues and consistent language to build an accurate picture of a brand. Without schema, entity definitions, disambiguation, internal linking patterns and external signals, AI systems often misinterpret who you are, what you do and whether you are credible enough to cite. This is why many strong brands are simply not appearing in AI answers yet.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">What will GEO actually change on my website?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>GEO touches content, structure, metadata, schema, topical relationships and how your brand is represented off site. We refine key pages so they follow natural language patterns that suit LLM interpretation. We apply structured data and entity markup that clarifies products, services, people and locations. We fix ambiguity and improve internal referencing. The goal is to make your website easy for an AI system to understand, not just a search crawler.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                              <div data-question-group>\n                          <div class=\"flex gap-4 mb-4\" data-question-ask>\n                            <strong>Did this answer your question?<\/strong>\n                            <span class=\"relative text-green cursor-pointer\" data-question=\"yes\">\n                        