                           <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Do AI engines use backlinks, and does GEO involve link building?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>AI engines do not treat backlinks the same way as Google does in traditional rankings. They do, however, use external references, citations and trusted sources as signals of authority. GEO link building is not about chasing domain authority. It is about acquiring citations and mentions that strengthen your brand entity, reinforce topical expertise and give AI systems more confidence in referencing your content inside answers.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">How long does it take to see results from GEO?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>Most brands see initial improvements within the first month once technical and structural issues are fixed. Stronger gains come as content is reshaped, entity signals mature and citation work builds authority. AI generated answers update quickly in some platforms and slowly in others. Timeframes vary, but most clients see meaningful movement within the first twelve weeks and ongoing gains as reinforcement continues.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Will GEO affect my traditional SEO performance?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>In most cases, GEO strengthens SEO because it improves clarity, intent, internal structure and topical relationships. Structured data, entity mapping, improved copy and clearer service definitions benefit both AI platforms and search engines. GEO is not a replacement for SEO. It is an expansion that prepares your website for a search environment that is moving toward summarisation and entity led visibility.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                              <div data-question-group>\n                          <div class=\"flex gap-4 mb-4\" data-question-ask>\n                            <strong>Did this answer your question?<\/strong>\n                            <span class=\"relative text-green cursor-pointer\" data-question=\"yes\">\n                              Yes\n                              <div class=\"faq-pop-up\" data-question-display=\"yes\">\n                                That\u2019s great glad we could help!\n                                <a href=\"\/contact-us\/\" target=\"_self\" class=\"btn btn-pink btn-small\" data-mp=\"\">\n                                  <span class=\"btn-bg\" data-mp-item=\"\" data-mp-scale=\"1.05\" data-mp-d=\"0.2\"><\/span>\n                                  <span class=\"btn-label\" data-mp-item=\"\">\n                                                                          Start a Project                                                                      <\/span>\n                                <\/a>\n                              <\/div>\n                            <\/span>\n                            <span class=\"relative text-red cursor-pointer\" data-question=\"no\">\n                              No\n                              <div class=\"faq-pop-up\" data-question-display=\"no\">\n                                No problem, one of our experts can give you a more in-depth answer.\n                                <a href=\"\/contact-us\/\" target=\"_self\" class=\"btn btn-pink btn-small\" data-mp=\"\">\n                                  <span class=\"btn-bg\" data-mp-item=\"\" data-mp-scale=\"1.05\" data-mp-d=\"0.2\"><\/span>\n                                  <span class=\"btn-label\" data-mp-item=\"\">Ask our Experts<\/span>\n                                <\/a>\n                              <\/div>\n                            <\/span>\n                          <\/div>\n                        <\/div>\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">How do you measure success with GEO when AI engines do not provide analytics?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>We track brand mentions, citations, inclusion in AI summaries, visibility within conversational search tools, LLM queries and downstream behaviour like traffic, engagement and conversions. We also monitor keyword groups that are likely to trigger summaries and assess whether your brand is being cited. While analytics are early, the industry now has reliable ways of monitoring AI driven visibility and influence across platforms.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Will GEO help with Google\u2019s AI Overviews and Microsoft Copilot results?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>Yes. Both systems are entity focused and rely heavily on structured data, clarity and trusted references. If your content is not LLM friendly, you are unlikely to appear in these summaries even if you rank well in organic results. GEO improves the signals these AI engines use to decide which brands to feature inside their generated responses.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Is GEO suitable for small businesses, or is it only for larger brands?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>Any brand that relies on search visibility benefits from GEO. Smaller brands often gain the most because AI engines flatten the playing field. If you have stronger entity clarity and better authority signals than larger competitors, AI systems may cite you regardless of domain authority. GEO is one of the few areas in digital marketing where small brands can move faster than big ones.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                              <div data-question-group>\n                          <div class=\"flex gap-4 mb-4\" data-question-ask>\n                            <strong>Did this answer your question?<\/strong>\n                            <span class=\"relative text-green cursor-pointer\" data-question=\"yes\">\n                              Yes\n                              <div class=\"faq-pop-up\" data-question-display=\"yes\">\n                                That\u2019s great glad we could help!\n                                <a href=\"\/contact-us\/\" target=\"_self\" class=\"btn btn-pink btn-small\" data-mp=\"\">\n                                  <span class=\"btn-bg\" data-mp-item=\"\" data-mp-scale=\"1.05\" data-mp-d=\"0.2\"><\/span>\n  